f you want to use your skills and training to do something important, send your resume and apply today. Referentia Systems, an applied R&D company, provides certified & accredited enterprise solutions for Federal clients. Founded in 1996, Referentia is an award-winning, small business headquartered in Honolulu, Hawaii, with staff across the country focused on delivering reliable and effective cybersecurity services and solutions. JOB SUMMARY Seasoned IT budget professional to support large scale enterprise IT capital planning, budgeting and compliance efforts Duties Develops scheduled enterprise IT capital and budget plans by working with many departments/groups to collect and validate IT budgeting information. Reviews and reports on performance of departments/groups and their expenditures against the plan. Provides analysis of metrics collected on various IT related budget and compliance items for senior leadership. Evaluates existing planning and budgeting processes to identify improvements and implements those improvements to make the annual financial planning more efficient and understandable to the enterprise. Qualifications Bachelor\u2019s degree in an accounting, finance, or related field. Master\u2019s degree preferred. 5+yrs. (Mid-Level) 10+ yrs. (Senior Level) demonstrated experience in IT capital planning and budgeting. Experience in program/project management preferred. Experienced with data analytic tools (Tableau software and Oracle Business Intelligence preferred). Experience with IT Investment Portfolio Suite (ITIPS) experience preferred. Knowledge of Planning, Programming, Budget and Execution (PPB&E) DoD Directive 7045.14 preferred (Senior Level). Ability to assess customer needs and translate to business case. Understands processes, key measurements, operating level targets, etc. Excellent, clear and concise communication skills, both oral and written, necessary to present ideas, to collaborate effectively, and to gain influence at all levels of the organization. Must have a Secret Level security clearance. Excellent Benefits: Referentia provides a comprehensive set of benefits to our employees, including generous health care, time off and retirement coverage, as well as tuition reimbursement and more.We are currently looking for talented, team oriented and dedicated professionals who share our passion for quality, innovation, and cybersecurity. If this is you, then Referentia may be a perfect fit! Submit your resume to apply for this job. We are proud to be an Equal Employment Opportunity Employer. Job Types: Full-time, Contract Pay: $0.00 per hour Experience: program or project management: 1 year (Preferred) IT Capital Planning, Budgeting: 5 years (Required) Education: Bachelor's (Required) License: Secret security level clearance (Required) Work Location: One location Benefits: Health insurance Dental insurance Vision insurance Retirement plan Paid time off Professional development assistance Tuition reimbursement Schedule: Monday to Friday Day shift Work Remotely: No "
